# React Frontend Structure

## Main Entry Points
- **Admin Interface**: [src/admin/index.js](mdc:dokan-chatbot/src/admin/index.js)
- **Chatbot Widget**: [src/chatbot/index.js](mdc:dokan-chatbot/src/chatbot/index.js)

## Key Components
- [src/chatbot/components/ChatbotWidget.js](mdc:dokan-chatbot/src/chatbot/components/ChatbotWidget.js): Main chatbot UI container.
- [src/chatbot/components/ChatbotMessages.js](mdc:dokan-chatbot/src/chatbot/components/ChatbotMessages.js): Displays chat messages.
- [src/chatbot/components/ChatbotInput.js](mdc:dokan-chatbot/src/chatbot/components/ChatbotInput.js): User input field for sending messages.
- [src/chatbot/components/ChatbotSuggestions.js](mdc:dokan-chatbot/src/chatbot/components/ChatbotSuggestions.js): Suggested prompts for users.
- [src/chatbot/components/ChatbotHistory.js](mdc:dokan-chatbot/src/chatbot/components/ChatbotHistory.js): Shows previous chat sessions.

## Backend Integration
- The React frontend communicates with the backend via the REST API defined in [includes/Chatbot/REST/ChatbotController.php](mdc:dokan-chatbot/includes/Chatbot/REST/ChatbotController.php).
- Handles chat message sending, receiving, and context updates.

Refer to this rule for understanding and navigating the React-based frontend and its integration with the backend AI logic.
